{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"59b4e5d4-9c11-4136-9fc0-eecf08e078fd","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net 2.9.3 project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Replace the test runner package:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\n**2. Add the MSBuild property** (in your `.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Optionally enable the new output** (for `dotnet test`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformShowTestsFailure>true</TestingPlatformShowTestsFailure>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Run tests** the same way:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (a key MTP feature):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project YourTests.csproj -- --help\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (or `xunit.v3`) and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` as before.\n- The `xunit.runner.mtp` package bridges xUnit.net to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- No code changes needed — only package/project file changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"651d355c-9f66-48f8-928f-f23c92590166","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":427,"requestId":"E3F6:7A682:15E5DA1:187DDF9:6A051F52"},"id":"08b0750b-c29d-4255-b1a6-74257561599d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:03:25.598Z","parentId":"15b73639-d31e-44c4-bf69-888c5661e328"}
